BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: BOYS & GIRLS CLUBS OF VOLUSIA FLAGLER

IRS990.Desc: THE CLUBS ARE WELL LOCATED AND POSITIONED TO MAKE AN IMPACT ON THE KIDS, FAMILIES, AND COMMUNITIES WHO MOST NEED THEIR SERVICES AND PROGRAMS. DURING 2022, THE CLUBS SERVED 1,339 YOUTH. THE PERCENTAGE OF CLUB MEMBERS FROM SINGLE PARENT/NONTRADITONAL HOMES WAS 71%. 94% OF CLUB MEMBERS MET FAMILY INCOME QUALIFICATIONS FOR FREE/REDUCED SCHOOL LUNCHES.100% OF CLUB MEMBERS RECEIVED ACADEMIC ASSISTANCE. 100%OF CLUB MEMBERS PARTICIPATED IN PREVENTION PROGRAMS WHICH EMPOWER AND EDUCATE YOUTH TO MAKE RIGHT DECISIONS ABOUT ALCOHOL, DRUG AND TOBACCO USE AND PREMARITAL SEXUAL ACTIVITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: B&GCV-F IS THE SOLE CONTRACTED GRANTEE AND RECIPIENT OF ALL GRANT FUNDS AWARDED BY THE COUNTY OF VOLUSIA FOR AFTER SCHOOL K-12 YOUTH DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES. B&GCV-F SUBSEQUENTLY AWARDS A PORTION OF THE GRANT FUNDS IT RECEIVES TO A PRE-SELECTED LIST OF OTHER PROVIDERS OF AFTER-SCHOOL PROGRAMS BASED ON THEIR FULFILLMENT OF THE GRANT REQUIREMENTS. B&GCV-F HAS SOLE DISCRETION AND CONTROL OVER THE DISBURSEMENT OF ALL FUNDS TO SUB-GRANTEES. B&GCV-F IS SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE GRANT AND MONITORS THE SUB-GRANTEES, WHICH INCLUDES SCHEDULED PERIODIC ON-SITE REVIEWS OF PROGRAM COMPONENTS, YOUTH PARTICIPATION, FACILITIES, DOCUMENTATION, REPORTS, PERSONNEL, TRAINING, SAFETY, ADMINISTRATION, FINANCIAL REPORTING, ORGANIZATIONAL OVERSIGHT, AND PROGRAM OUTCOMES. MONITORING REPORTS AND EVALUATIONS ARE PROVIDED TO THE COUNTY OF VOLUSIA. B&GCV-F RETAINS APPROXIMATELY 4.4% OF THE GRANT FUNDS IT RECEIVES FOR ADMINISTRATION AND MONITORING.

ANY BOARD OF DIRECTOR WITH A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS PROHIBITED FROM VOTING ON THAT ISSUE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 - ORGANIZATIONS MISSION OR MOST SIGNIFICANT ACTIVITIESTO INSPIRE AND ENABLE ALL YOUNG PEOPLE, ESPECIALLY THOSE FROM DISADVANTAGED CIRCUMSTANCES, TO REALIZE THEIR FULLEST POTENTIAL AS PRODUCTIVE, RESPONSIBLE AND CARING CITIZENS AND LEADERS. ORGANIZATIONAL FOCUS: TO SERVE BOYS AND GIRLS AGES 6-19 WITH EMPHASIS ON OUTREACH TO TEENS, GENDER INCLUSION AND FAMILY INVOLVEMENT. CORE PROGRAM: CHARACTER AND LEADERSHIP DEVELOPMENT; EDUCATIONAL AND CAREERDEVELOPMENT; HEALTH AND LIFE SKILLS; THE ARTS; AND SPORTS, FITNESS AND RECREATION.FORM 990, PART VI, LINE 10B - POLICIES AND PROCEDURES GOVERNING CHAPTERSTHE ORGANIZATIONS BOARD ROUTINELY SETS POLICIES AND PROCEDURES FOR EACH OFTHEIR CLUBS. INSTRUMENTAL TO THE ORGANIZATIONS MISSION AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS ARE IN-KIND SERVICES AND CONTRIBUTED FACILITIES. FOR 2022 THE ORGANIZATIONS IN-KIND CONTRIBUTIONS FOR SERVICES AND FACILITIES WERE AS FOLLOWS:SERVICES - ADVERTISING WITH VALUE OF $46,620; REPAIRS AND MAINTENANCE WITH A VALUE OF $12,315; OTHER WITH A VALUE OF $9,024 FACILITIES - DONATED OR REDUCED COST RENTS AND UTILITIES FOR SEVEN LOCATIONS WITH A VALUE OF $218,028
